From: aorus-5090-egpu <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] AORUS Lever M-recover Commit 3 (Patch 0024) — H1/H2/H3/H4 hardened

Patch 0024 implements the Commit 3 recovery action with all four
hardening fixes baked in from line 1 (per the 2026-05-06 storm postmortem).

H1 MaxAttempts gate: atomic_inc_return on attempt_count compared against
    NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMMaxAttempts BEFORE scheduling work. Surrender path
    increments surrender_count + emits TB_EGPU_GPU_STATE=PERMANENT_FAIL
    uevent. attempt_count resets on successful slot_reset/resume OR
    after NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMSurrenderResetSec idle (5 min default).

H2 Rate-limit gate: refuses to schedule a new attempt if the previous
    fire was less than NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMMinAttemptIntervalMs ago
    (30 s default). Defends against AER bursts and recovery storms.

H3 Kill-switch persistence: driver reads
    /var/lib/aorus-egpu/lever-m-killswitch at module init via
    kernel_read_file_from_path; if present and content is '0', forces
    NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable to 0 even if the user passed
    Enable=1 cmdline. Userspace CLI (aorus-egpu-lever-m enable/disable/status)
    plus a udev rule at module-add time provide defense-in-depth.

H4 Smarter error_detected: NEEDS_RESET path engages when Enable=1 +
    attempts<Max + rate-limit OK; surrender / rate-limit / disabled
    paths return DISCONNECT and let the existing M-base cleanup chain
    run. nv_pci_slot_reset / nv_pci_resume callbacks handle the
    kernel-driven recovery branch — verify PMC_BOOT_0 (RECOVERED or
    DISCONNECT), then on resume increment success_count, reset
    attempt_count to 0, emit READY uevent.

Trigger sharpened (post-storm): post-rmInit-FAIL with WPR2!=0, NOT
    probe-time. Hooked at nv_start_device after rm_init_adapter
    returns failure, just before rc=-EIO. Probe-time check from
    Patch 0017 is preserved as a no-op-detection sanity check
    (per docs convention — falsified-but-illustrative).

Default OFF (NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable=0). Validate Enable=1
    cmdline override in test phases BEFORE flipping the default to 1.

Userspace artefacts (in repo):
  usr/local/sbin/aorus-egpu-lever-m                    — kill-switch CLI
  usr/local/sbin/aorus-egpu-lever-m-killswitch-restore — udev RUN+= helper
  etc/udev/rules.d/82-aorus-egpu-lever-m-killswitch.rules

Test plan (from design doc):
  Phase 1: build verification (modinfo new params)
  Phase 2: cold-boot baseline with Enable=0 (regression check)
  Phase 3: NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMTestForceTrigger=1 — exercise recovery path
  Phase 4: discrete H1/H2/H3/H4 hardening tests
  Phase 5: n>=10 PROVEN cold-cold-boot recoveries → retire
           aorus-egpu-wpr2-recovery.service

References: docs/lever-m-recover-commit3-hardening-design.md
            docs/lever-M-recover-design.md
            archive/commit3-recovery-loop-2026-05-06-161429/
Hypothesis ledger: H13, H15.
